The reason we think that this code is unsafe is due to the fact that it uses a non-canonical format for the position table.
A position table is a table that is built to store the position and size of each element in the table.
In a canonical position table, the size of the element is stored in the first 4 bytes of the element and the position of the element is stored in the next 4 bytes of the element.
The elements are then sorted based on the position of the elements.
A malicious user can build a non-canonical position table where the size of the element is stored in the last 4 bytes of the element and the position of the element is stored in the first 4 bytes of the element.
